Jubilee aspirants in Mombasa have been assured of free and fair nominations.Deputy President William Ruto on Sunday said some aspirants fear they will be locked out through favouritism in the party owing to seniority, financial muscle and closeness to the President and the DP. Supporters of governor aspirant Ananiah Mwaboza had been growing uneasy with fellow aspirant Suleiman Shahbal, who has been growing closer to Ruto.Mwaboza also has unlimited access to Ruto, being his special adviser on parliamentary affairs.